postcontent: This Norinco MAK90 is in great shape and has worked flawlessly for me. Norinco AK's are great quality rifles....built with a thicker receiver than standard AK's and also have chrome lined barrels not found in many of the commercially available AK's that come in parts kits. I bought this MAK90 with the thumbhole stock. I removed the thumbhole stock and converted it into what you see. Fully 922(r) compliant (US parts count) compliant. I installed a Tapco G2 fire control group and put a Custom Ironwood Designs furniture kit on it ($200+). I dyed the custom wood a "Russian Red". Authentic Norinco butt stock and handguards along with thumbhole stock and a black Arsenal polymer pistol grip also come with rifle so you have options as to how you want dress it up. 5 mags come with rifle (3 foreign surplus steel mags, 2 Tapco G2 polymer mags), I have one more surplus mag that I can't seem to find at the moment, if I happen to find it then its yours as well. I have installed Aresenal US made mag followers in the foreign mags just to add another US made part for part count reasons, the original mag followers are included. Also included is an extra Norinco firing pin still in packaging, extra pistol grip screw still in packaging, an an unused Hoppes boresnake for the 7.62x39 caliber, and the Russian sling you see pictured. Everything pictured comes with the rifle in addition to 900rds of recent production Tula 7.62x39 ammo in an ammo can. The ammo isn't pictured because it is at the bottom of my safe with many other boxes of ammo stored on top of it. I believe we have all seen an ammo can before. I'm asking $800 for the entire package (rifle, accessories, ammo). Price is firm. Buyer must have a valid NE state ID AND either a valid NE Conceal Carry license or purchase permit. title: For Sale:  DuraCoat Firearm Finish - Aerosol Can with Hardener - Matte Black - New & Unused
location: Lower Bucks County, Pennsylvania, United States
postcontent:
I have one aerosol can of DuraCoat Firearm Finish in the solid Matte Black color that I would like to sell. This aerosol can is completely new and unused.

My asking price is $30 for this aerosol can of DuraCoat. 

My price is firm on this, because I paid higher price myself than this. I also had to pay a high Hazmat shipping and handling fee for just this one can of DuraCoat.

I will meet you face to face in Lower Bucks County for a cash-only transaction. 

I will ship this item if you really want me to, but this item can only be shipped with all applicable Hazmat fees.

DuraCoat is much more than just some "paint" from a hardware store. I have not yet seen these products being sold at any stores, or even at any gun shows, either.

DuraCoat aerosol cans have a unique can-within-a-can feature which provides the hardener right inside the can.  No measuring or mixing is necessary to use this item. You instead just shake the can for two minutes, then release the hardener by activating the catalyst inside the can, and then shake the can again for two more minutes, and then you will be ready to apply the spray. 

DuraCoat will provide protection against rust and corrosion, plus excellent protection from UV rays of the sun. DuraCoat can be applied to all types of metal, plastic, and wood. DuraCoat can be applied over bare metal, parkerized finishes, anodized finishes, and blued finishes.  

This can of aerosol DuraCoat will remain usable for up to 48 hours once activated. This can of aerosol DuraCoat contains enough material to cover 2 entire rifles or 4 entire handguns, or 1 entire rifle and 2 entire handguns. DuraCoat can be used on almost anything else besides guns, too...things like paintball guns, bows, crossbows, knife or machete blades, ATV or truck parts, etc.

No baking or preheating is required to use DuraCoat. This can of DuraCoat has an adjustable nozzle for vertical or horizontal spraying.

If you would like to see an official product demonstration for a can of aerosol DuraCoat, you can view the Youtube video for it here:

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_onlukWppJU

Please contact me with any questions that you may have.

Please check out my other listings here on Armslist. Thanks!

NOTE: If you want me to send a text message to your cell phone, I can do this if you would please tell me what carrier your cell phone is with. (Verizon/AT&T/Sprint/T-Mobile/?) I need to know this because then I can send a text to your cell phone with my textem account, which I log into with my computer.
